HEADWORD: Suspensorium
<hw>Sus`pen*so"ri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Suspensoria</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[NL.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Anything which suspends or
holds up a part: especially, the mandibular suspensorium (a series of
bones, or of cartilages representing them) which connects the base of
the lower jaw with the skull in most vertebrates below
mammals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suspensory</ent>⟦br⟧
